23/07/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor confirmed on Wednesday (July 22nd) that the cabinet plans to introduce a temporary tax to boost budget revenues during the economic crisis.
The rate will be 5-6%, down from 8% as initially proposed.
The new tax on salaries and pensions would take effect next month, and run through the end of next year.
(Javno - 23/07/09;
AP, HINA, HRT - 22/07/09)
